<dl id="n54078g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54078g">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54078g"> 78(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> saints de glace / poilu,</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Today, in many countries, these critical dates&mdash;the feasts of Saint George, Marc, Vital, Eutrope, etc&mdash;are designated under the name of <i><mark>saints de glace</mark></i>]</font> &hellip; p303: <font color="green">[Remarks of the expression <i>&agrave; tout le poil</i>, applied to Pantagruel, meaning strong and vigorous, capable of anything. This expression recurs in &ldquo;<mark>les Poilus</mark> de la grande Guerre&rdquo;.]</font> <small> L. Sainean, <a name="LSLR" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LSLR"><cite title="source">La Langue de Rabelais</cite></a> (1922) I (Rites et Croyances) 300</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See also <a name="n54050f" href="n54all.htm#n54050f">N54 (VI.B.45):050(f)</a>. </mm> </dd></dl>
